Data Preprocessing

Reading in and storing dataset from file

d <- read.csv("nbasample2GrpPlus0429.csv",header=T, sep=",")

Removing ax_ and la_ variales, as requested

a <- colnames(d)
AX <- grepl("ax_",a) #seeing which values have prefix ax_
AXN <- c() #creating temporary vector recording positions
for(i in 1:length(a)){ #getting rejected values
  if(AX[i]){
    AXN <- c(AXN,i)
  }
}
d <- d[,-AXN] #removing rejected values
a <- colnames(d)
LA <- grepl("la_",a)
LAN <- c() #creating temporary vector recording positions
for(i in 1:length(a)){ #getting rejected values
  if(LA[i]){
    LAN <- c(LAN,i)
  }
}
d <- d[,-LAN] #removing rejected values
a <- colnames(d)
#Cleaning up Environment
rm(AX,AXN,LA,LAN)

Removing other Variables

#closest_arena and closest_team are identical - removing closest_arena
x <- match("closest_arena",a)
#x
d <- d[,-x]
a <- colnames(d)
#match("closest_arena",a) #successfully removed

#names(Filter(is.factor, d)) #taking a look at which variables have factors - tree() can only handle 32 levels on factor predictors

#zip_team and zip_arena have 56 levels - too many to grow trees on - removing both
x <- match(c("zip_team","zip_arena"),a)
#x
d <- d[,-x]
a <- colnames(d)
#match(c("zip_team","zip_arena"),a) #successfully removed
#email_domain has 1468 levels - too many.. -removing
x <- match(c("email_domain"),a)
#x
d <- d[,-x]
a <- colnames(d)
#match(c("email_domain"),a) #successfully removed
#source_date has 3773 levels - too many.. -removing
x <- match(c("source_date"),a)
#x
d <- d[,-x]
a <- colnames(d)
#match(c("source_date"),a) #successfully removed

Making a training/test set vector

train <- sample(1:nrow(d), nrow(d)*(.8))

Viewing Response Variables

POST <- grepl("post_",a)
POSTN <- c()
for(i in 1:length(a)){ #getting rejected values
  if(POST[i]){
    POSTN <- c(POSTN,i)
  }
}
#POSTN
a[POSTN]
##  [1] "post_ticket_response"        "post_tickets_flag"          
##  [3] "post_total_ticket_amt"       "post_total_tickets"         
##  [5] "post_avg_ticket_price"       "post_regular_season_tix"    
##  [7] "post_playoffs_tix"           "post_arc_flag"              
##  [9] "post_tmc_flag"               "post_tmc_resale_flag"       
## [11] "post_vtx_flag"               "post_vtx_flash_flag"        
## [13] "post_ticket_package_arc"     "post_ticket_package_derived"
## [15] "post_total_tickets_cat"

Given this dataset, a few useful questions can be answered: A - Who buys tickets? Successful or unsuccessful marketting strategies can be identified.

B - How many tickets do people buy? Besides success of strategy; if a person is likely to buy more tickets than they have purchased, they can likely be sold more tickets.

C - How much money do people spend on tickets? Same rationale as B, but with dollar-value rather than number of games.

D - Who buys tickets at which price? Better seats can be marketted more to those who are more likely to buy them.

A - Who buys tickets?

Removing other response variables besides post_tickets_flag

Q <- match('post_tickets_flag',a)
a[Q]
## [1] "post_tickets_flag"
POSTN_ptf <- POSTN[! POSTN %in% Q]
#POSTN_ptf
a[POSTN_ptf]
##  [1] "post_ticket_response"        "post_total_ticket_amt"      
##  [3] "post_total_tickets"          "post_avg_ticket_price"      
##  [5] "post_regular_season_tix"     "post_playoffs_tix"          
##  [7] "post_arc_flag"               "post_tmc_flag"              
##  [9] "post_tmc_resale_flag"        "post_vtx_flag"              
## [11] "post_vtx_flash_flag"         "post_ticket_package_arc"    
## [13] "post_ticket_package_derived" "post_total_tickets_cat"
dataset.ptf <- d[,-POSTN_ptf]

Growing Trees Creating pure Classification Response Vector

#Finding response vector
a.ptf <- colnames(dataset.ptf)
resp.ptf <- grepl("post_",a.ptf)
for(i in 1:length(a.ptf)){
  if(resp.ptf[i]){
    R <- i
  }
}
a.ptf[R]
## [1] "post_tickets_flag"
#Converting it to a yes/no factor
y <- post_tickets_flag
Ticket <- ifelse(y<0.5,"No","Yes")
dataset.ptf[,R] <- Ticket
dataset.ptf[,R] <- factor(dataset.ptf[,R])

Growing Preliminary Classification Tree

tree.ptf <- tree(post_tickets_flag~., dataset.ptf)
plot(tree.ptf)
text(tree.ptf,pretty=0)

Estimate Error Rate

tree.ptf_train <- tree(post_tickets_flag~., dataset.ptf, subset=train)
plot(tree.ptf_train)
text(tree.ptf_train,pretty=0)

tree.ptf_pred <- predict(tree.ptf_train, dataset.ptf[-train,], type="class")
M <- table(tree.ptf_pred, post_tickets_flag[-train])
M
##              
## tree.ptf_pred  No Yes
##           No  901 148
##           Yes  93 858
print(paste("The test error rate is", ((M[1,2]+M[2,1])/(sum(M)))))
## [1] "The test error rate is 0.1205"

Pruning the Tree

cv.ptf_train <- cv.tree(tree.ptf_train, FUN=prune.misclass)
cv.ptf_train
## $size
## [1] 11  9  8  4  2  1
## 
## $dev
## [1]  975 1093 1308 1399 1475 3579
## 
## $k
## [1]    -Inf   57.50   69.00   73.75   80.50 2104.00
## 
## $method
## [1] "misclass"
## 
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "prune"         "tree.sequence"
b <- which.min(cv.ptf_train$dev)
Best <- cv.ptf_train$size[b]
print(paste("The best trees seem to be of size",cv.ptf_train$size[b],"with cross-validation error of",cv.ptf_train$dev[b]))
## [1] "The best trees seem to be of size 11 with cross-validation error of 975"
prune.ptf_train <- prune.misclass(tree.ptf_train, best=Best)
plot(prune.ptf_train)
text(prune.ptf_train,pretty=0)

prune.ptf_pred <- predict(prune.ptf_train, dataset.ptf[-train,], type="class")
M_prune <- table(prune.ptf_pred, post_tickets_flag[-train])
M_prune
##               
## prune.ptf_pred  No Yes
##            No  901 148
##            Yes  93 858
print(paste("The test error rate is", ((M_prune[1,2]+M_prune[2,1])/(sum(M_prune)))))
## [1] "The test error rate is 0.1205"
print("Same error rate.")
## [1] "Same error rate."

bag.ptf_train <- randomForest(post_tickets_flag~., data=dataset.ptf0, subset=train, mtry=ncol(dataset.ptf0)-1, ntrees=1000, importance=TRUE)
bag.ptf_pred <- predict(bag.ptf_train, dataset.ptf0[-train,], type="class")
M_bag <- table(bag.ptf_pred, post_tickets_flag[-train])
M_bag
##             
## bag.ptf_pred  No Yes
##          No  881  90
##          Yes 113 916
print(paste("The test error rate is", ((M_bag[1,2]+M_bag[2,1])/(sum(M_bag)))))
## [1] "The test error rate is 0.1015"
print("About 90% accurate!")
## [1] "About 90% accurate!"

dataset.ptfB$post_tickets_flag <- y
#distribution='bernoulli' requires 0,1 variable
boost.ptf_train <- gbm(post_tickets_flag~., data=dataset.ptfB[train,], distribution='bernoulli', n.trees=1000, interaction.depth=4)
boost.ptf_pred <- predict(boost.ptf_train, dataset.ptfB[-train,], n.trees=1000)
M_boost <- table(boost.ptf_pred, post_tickets_flag[-train])

Growing Trees

Growing Preliminary Regression Tree

tree.ptt <- tree(post_total_tickets~., dataset.ptt)
plot(tree.ptt)
text(tree.ptt,pretty=0)

Estimate MSE

tree.ptt_train <- tree(post_total_tickets~., dataset.ptt, subset=train)
plot(tree.ptt_train)
text(tree.ptt_train,pretty=0)

tree.ptt_pred <- predict(tree.ptt_train, dataset.ptt[-train,])
plot(tree.ptt_pred, post_total_tickets[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.ptt <- mean((tree.ptt_pred-post_total_tickets[-train])^2)
MSE.ptt
## [1] 11.83655
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.ptt,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.ptt),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.ptt),1),"total tickets purchased. This is pretty bad, considering the vast majority seem to have bought fewer than 20 or so tickets total."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 11.8365472502529 . Root MSE is 3.44042835272774 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 3.4 total tickets purchased. This is pretty bad, considering the vast majority seem to have bought fewer than 20 or so tickets total."

Pruning the Tree

cv.ptt_train <- cv.tree(tree.ptt_train, FUN=prune.tree)
cv.ptt_train
## $size
## [1] 9 8 7 6 5 4 3 2 1
## 
## $dev
## [1]  70681.97  71144.28  71838.34  71624.94  71624.94  73502.06  81772.16
## [8]  87671.40 110500.27
## 
## $k
## [1]      -Inf  1242.559  1336.986  1414.245  1445.102  2245.138  6071.890
## [8]  8839.179 21258.429
## 
## $method
## [1] "deviance"
## 
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "prune"         "tree.sequence"
b <- which.min(cv.ptt_train$dev)
Best <- cv.ptt_train$size[b]
print(paste("The best trees seem to be of size",cv.ptt_train$size[b],"with deviation of",cv.ptt_train$dev[b],"."))
## [1] "The best trees seem to be of size 9 with deviation of 70681.969603896 ."
prune.ptt_train <- prune.tree(tree.ptt_train, best=Best)
plot(prune.ptt_train)
text(prune.ptt_train,pretty=0)

prune.ptt_pred <- predict(prune.ptt_train, dataset.ptt[-train,])
plot(prune.ptt_pred, post_total_tickets[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.prune.ptt <- mean((prune.ptt_pred-post_total_tickets[-train])^2)
MSE.prune.ptt
## [1] 11.83655
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.prune.ptt,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.prune.ptt),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.prune.ptt),1),"total tickets purchased. Successfully pruned, but still pretty bad."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 11.8365472502529 . Root MSE is 3.44042835272774 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 3.4 total tickets purchased. Successfully pruned, but still pretty bad."

Creating Bagged Tree

#Creating a modified dataset - na values are not accepted in bagged trees

dataset.ptt0[is.na(dataset.ptt0)] <- 0

bag.ptt_train <- randomForest(post_total_tickets~., data=dataset.ptt0, subset=train, mtry=ncol(dataset.ptt0)-1, ntrees=1000, importance=TRUE)
bag.ptt_pred <- predict(bag.ptt_train, dataset.ptt0[-train,])
plot(bag.ptt_pred, post_total_tickets[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.bag.ptt <- mean((bag.ptt_pred-post_total_tickets[-train])^2)
MSE.bag.ptt
## [1] 10.89291
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.bag.ptt,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.bag.ptt),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.bag.ptt),1),"total tickets purchased. No dice."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 10.8929140635512 . Root MSE is 3.30044149524744 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 3.3 total tickets purchased. No dice."

Creating Random Forest Tree

RF.ptt_train <- randomForest(post_total_tickets~., data=dataset.ptt0, subset=train, importance=TRUE)

Creating a Boosted Tree

#Creating a modified dataset - columns with no variation are not accepted in boosted trees
dataset.pttB <- dataset.ptt
colnames(dataset.pttB)[c(36,56)]
## [1] "ind_events_allstar_1y" "pre_pac"
dataset.pttB <- dataset.pttB[,-c(36,56)]
## The following objects are masked from dataset.ptt0:
## 
##     agecat, arenadis, closest_arena_150, closest_arena_75,
##     closest_arena_distance, closest_team, closeteam, Conference,
##     days_since_most_recent_click, days_since_most_recent_email,
##     days_since_most_recent_open, Division, emaildays,
##     ever_emailed, fan_total_amt_l12, fan_total_amt_l24,

boost.ptt_train <- gbm(post_total_tickets~., data=dataset.pttB[train,], distribution='gaussian', n.trees=1000, interaction.depth=4)
boost.ptt_pred <- predict(boost.ptt_train, dataset.pttB[-train,], n.trees=1000)
plot(boost.ptt_pred, post_total_tickets[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.boost.ptt <- mean((boost.ptt_pred-post_total_tickets[-train])^2)
MSE.boost.ptt
## [1] 11.93671
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.boost.ptt,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.boost.ptt),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.boost.ptt),1),"total tickets purchased. Still not good enough."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 11.936708527275 . Root MSE is 3.45495420045983 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 3.5 total tickets purchased. Still not good enough."

C - How much money do people spend on tickets?

Growing Trees

Growing Preliminary Regression Tree

tree.ptta <- tree(post_total_ticket_amt~., dataset.ptta)
plot(tree.ptta)
text(tree.ptta,pretty=0)

Estimate MSE

tree.ptta_train <- tree(post_total_ticket_amt~., dataset.ptta, subset=train)
plot(tree.ptta_train)
text(tree.ptta_train,pretty=0)

tree.ptta_pred <- predict(tree.ptta_train, dataset.ptta[-train,])
plot(tree.ptta_pred, post_total_ticket_amt[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.ptta <- mean((tree.ptta_pred-post_total_ticket_amt[-train])^2)
MSE.ptta
## [1] 309426.3
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.ptta,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.ptta),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.ptta),1),"total tickets purchased. This is pretty bad, considering the vast majority seem to have bought fewer than 20 or so tickets total."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 309426.332798279 . Root MSE is 556.261029372254 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 556.3 total tickets purchased. This is pretty bad, considering the vast majority seem to have bought fewer than 20 or so tickets total."

Pruning the Tree

cv.ptta_train <- cv.tree(tree.ptta_train, FUN=prune.tree)
cv.ptta_train
## $size
## [1] 6 5 4 3 2 1
## 
## $dev
## [1] 3331028971 3389256036 3413168345 3614311619 3866372935 3729662963
## 
## $k
## [1]      -Inf  61612450  79246324 251163009 617420832 698965399
## 
## $method
## [1] "deviance"
## 
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "prune"         "tree.sequence"
b <- which.min(cv.ptta_train$dev)
Best <- cv.ptta_train$size[b]
print(paste("The best trees seem to be of size",cv.ptta_train$size[b],"with deviation of",cv.ptta_train$dev[b],"."))
## [1] "The best trees seem to be of size 6 with deviation of 3331028971.33953 ."
prune.ptta_train <- prune.tree(tree.ptta_train, best=Best)
plot(prune.ptta_train)
text(prune.ptta_train,pretty=0)

prune.ptta_pred <- predict(prune.ptta_train, dataset.ptta[-train,])
plot(prune.ptta_pred, post_total_ticket_amt[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.prune.ptta <- mean((prune.ptta_pred-post_total_ticket_amt[-train])^2)
MSE.prune.ptta
## [1] 309426.3
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.prune.ptta,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.prune.ptta),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.prune.ptta),1),"total tickets purchased. Successfully pruned, but still pretty bad."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 309426.332798279 . Root MSE is 556.261029372254 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 556.3 total tickets purchased. Successfully pruned, but still pretty bad."

Creating Bagged Tree

#Creating a modified dataset - na values are not accepted in bagged trees
dataset.ptta0 <- dataset.ptta
dataset.ptta0[is.na(dataset.ptta0)] <- 0

bag.ptta_train <- randomForest(post_total_ticket_amt~., data=dataset.ptta0, subset=train, mtry=ncol(dataset.ptta0)-1, ntrees=1000, importance=TRUE)
bag.ptta_pred <- predict(bag.ptta_train, dataset.ptta0[-train,])
plot(bag.ptta_pred, post_total_ticket_amt[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.bag.ptta <- mean((bag.ptta_pred-post_total_ticket_amt[-train])^2)
MSE.bag.ptta
## [1] 386375.4
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.bag.ptta,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.bag.ptta),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.bag.ptta),1),"total tickets purchased. No dice."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 386375.35465029 . Root MSE is 621.590986622466 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 621.6 total tickets purchased. No dice."

Looking at Predictor Importance

bag.I <- importance(bag.ptf_train)
bag.I <- bag.I[ order(bag.I[,3],decreasing=TRUE), ]
print("The fifteen most important predictors (by error) according to this model are as follows:")
## [1] "The fifteen most important predictors (by error) according to this model are as follows:"

Creating Random Forest Tree

RF.ptta_train <- randomForest(post_total_ticket_amt~., data=dataset.ptta0, subset=train, importance=TRUE)
RF.ptta_pred <- predict(RF.ptta_train, dataset.ptta0[-train,])
plot(RF.ptta_pred, post_total_ticket_amt[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.RF.ptta <- mean((RF.ptta_pred-post_total_ticket_amt[-train])^2)
MSE.RF.ptta
## [1] 361782.5
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.bag.ptta,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.RF.ptta),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.RF.ptta),1),"total tickets purchased. Best of so far, nothing good yet."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 386375.35465029 . Root MSE is 601.483543524871 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 601.5 total tickets purchased. Best of so far, nothing good yet."

boost.ptta_train <- gbm(post_total_ticket_amt~., data=dataset.pttaB[train,], distribution='gaussian', n.trees=1000, interaction.depth=4)
boost.ptta_pred <- predict(boost.ptta_train, dataset.pttaB[-train,], n.trees=1000)
plot(boost.ptta_pred, post_total_ticket_amt[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.boost.ptta <- mean((boost.ptta_pred-post_total_ticket_amt[-train])^2)
MSE.boost.ptta
## [1] 348982.2
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.boost.ptta,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.boost.ptta),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.boost.ptta),1),"total tickets purchased. Still not good enough."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 348982.197915014 . Root MSE is 590.747152269915 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 590.7 total tickets purchased. Still not good enough."

Growing Trees

Growing Preliminary Regression Tree

tree.patp <- tree(post_avg_ticket_price~., dataset.patp)
plot(tree.patp)
text(tree.patp,pretty=0)

Estimate MSE

tree.patp_train <- tree(post_avg_ticket_price~., dataset.patp, subset=train)
plot(tree.patp_train)
text(tree.patp_train,pretty=0)

tree.patp_pred <- predict(tree.patp_train, dataset.patp[-train,])
plot(tree.patp_pred, post_avg_ticket_price[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.patp <- mean((tree.patp_pred-post_avg_ticket_price[-train])^2)
MSE.patp
## [1] 12644.43
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.patp,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.patp),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.patp),1),"total tickets purchased. This is pretty bad, considering the vast majority seem to have bought fewer than 20 or so tickets total."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 12644.4269476081 . Root MSE is 112.447440822849 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 112.4 total tickets purchased. This is pretty bad, considering the vast majority seem to have bought fewer than 20 or so tickets total."

Pruning the Tree

cv.patp_train <- cv.tree(tree.patp_train, FUN=prune.tree)
cv.patp_train
## $size
## [1] 4 3 1
## 
## $dev
## [1] 191151188 196133472 214220975
## 
## $k
## [1]     -Inf  5107469 32079938
## 
## $method
## [1] "deviance"
## 
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "prune"         "tree.sequence"
b <- which.min(cv.patp_train$dev)
Best <- cv.patp_train$size[b]
print(paste("The best trees seem to be of size",cv.patp_train$size[b],"with deviation of",cv.patp_train$dev[b],"."))
## [1] "The best trees seem to be of size 4 with deviation of 191151188.200144 ."
prune.patp_train <- prune.tree(tree.patp_train, best=Best)
plot(prune.patp_train)
text(prune.patp_train,pretty=0)

prune.patp_pred <- predict(prune.patp_train, dataset.patp[-train,])
plot(prune.patp_pred, post_avg_ticket_price[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.prune.patp <- mean((prune.patp_pred-post_avg_ticket_price[-train])^2)
MSE.prune.patp
## [1] 12644.43
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.prune.patp,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.prune.patp),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.prune.patp),1),"total tickets purchased. Successfully pruned, but still pretty bad."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 12644.4269476081 . Root MSE is 112.447440822849 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 112.4 total tickets purchased. Successfully pruned, but still pretty bad."

bag.patp_train <- randomForest(post_avg_ticket_price~., data=dataset.patp0, subset=train, mtry=ncol(dataset.patp0)-1, ntrees=1000, importance=TRUE)
bag.patp_pred <- predict(bag.patp_train, dataset.patp0[-train,])
plot(bag.patp_pred, post_avg_ticket_price[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.bag.patp <- mean((bag.patp_pred-post_avg_ticket_price[-train])^2)
MSE.bag.patp
## [1] 18201.4
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.bag.patp,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.bag.patp),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.bag.patp),1),"total tickets purchased. No dice."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 18201.3976704181 . Root MSE is 134.912555644084 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 134.9 total tickets purchased. No dice."

boost.patp_train <- gbm(post_avg_ticket_price~., data=dataset.patpB[train,], distribution='gaussian', n.trees=1000, interaction.depth=4)
boost.patp_pred <- predict(boost.patp_train, dataset.patpB[-train,], n.trees=1000)
plot(boost.patp_pred, post_avg_ticket_price[-train])
abline(0,1)

MSE.boost.patp <- mean((boost.patp_pred-post_avg_ticket_price[-train])^2)
MSE.boost.patp
## [1] 16928.79
print(paste("Test MSE is",MSE.boost.patp,". Root MSE is",sqrt(MSE.boost.patp),", indicating this model leads to test predictions within around",round(sqrt(MSE.boost.patp),1),"total tickets purchased. Still not good enough."))
## [1] "Test MSE is 16928.7892057868 . Root MSE is 130.110680598431 , indicating this model leads to test predictions within around 130.1 total tickets purchased. Still not good enough."
